text.section:
A hospital may discharge a patient:
Entirely;
To another level of care, treatment, or services;
To different health professionals; or
To settings for continued services.

To facilitate discharge or transfer, the hospital shall:
Assess a patient's needs;
Plan for discharge or transfer;
Facilitate the discharge or transfer process;
Give the patient or person responsible for providing continuing care to the patient written discharge instructions in a form the patient can understand; and
Help to ensure that continuity of care, treatment, and services is maintained.
